article.headline: Florida A&M 73, Hampton 65
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Tony Tate had 22 points and eight assists and Florida A&M scored 20 of its 38 second-half points at the foul line Wednesday night to beat Hampton 73-65. Rome Sanders added 15 points and Brian Greene had 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Rattlers (13-15, 9-8 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). The Rattlers finished 22-for-26 at the foul line, outscoring Hampton 22-11, and outrebounded the Pirates 43-36. Hampton (12-15, 10-8) got 13 points from Junior Peroua and 11 from Bruce Brown.
